cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MA 

The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves optimization problems, such as machine scheduling and facility location, which fall under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of monitoring as a mechanism design paradigm involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and their incentives, which is a common theme in mechanism design.
